    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a strict filtering system.\n\nReturn ONLY JSON:\n{\n  \"fulfilment_related\": true/false\n}\n\nA review is ONLY \"true\" if it explicitly mentions ANY of:\n\n1. Logistics & shipping\n2. Delivery delay or speed\n3. Tracking issues\n4. Missing / wrong items\n5. Packaging damage\n6. Temperature / freshness / thawing\n7. Order fulfillment errors\n\nIf not explicitly mentioned → false\n\nDo NOT infer.\nDo NOT assume.\nDo NOT use sentiment.\n\nReview:\nTitle: {{ $json.title }}\nText: {{ $json.text }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "batching": {
            "batchSize": 5,
            "delayBetweenBatches": 5000
          }
        }
      },
      "id": "23055c8a-30b3-4316-8daf-2d37f6126cd3",
      "name": "Filter Fulfillment Reviews",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        1680,
        288
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "sortFieldsUi": {
          "sortField": [
            {
              "fieldName": "dates.publishedDate",
              "order": "descending"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "c4b853c6-824c-4f98-be61-4ac3075343ac",
      "name": "Sort by Date",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.sort",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        2256,
        400
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const inputItems = $input.all();\n\nconst fulfilmentItems = inputItems\n  .filter(i => i.json.fulfilment_related === true)\n  .sort((a, b) => {\n    const dateA = new Date(a.json.dates?.publishedDate || 0).getTime();\n    const dateB = new Date(b.json.dates?.publishedDate || 0).getTime();\n    return dateB - dateA; // newest first\n  });\n\nconst total = inputItems.length;\nconst fulfilmentCount = fulfilmentItems.length;\n\nreturn [\n  {\n    json: {\n      total_reviews: total,\n      fulfilment_relevant_reviews: fulfilmentCount,\n      has_fulfilment_signal: fulfilmentCount > 0,\n      fulfilment_items: fulfilmentItems.map(i => ({\n        title: i.json.title,\n        text: i.json.text,\n        rating: i.json.rating,\n        publishedDate: i.json.dates?.publishedDate,\n        businessUrl: i.json.businessUrl\n      }))\n    }\n  }\n];"
      },
      "id": "46a11131-c747-4c81-b1ef-6066c7d1770c",
      "name": "Count and Sort Fulfillment Reviews",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        2480,
        400
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "strict",
            "version": 3
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "c8464822-3f58-4b8f-a827-9d2f8678134f",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.fulfilment_relevant_reviews }}",
              "rightValue": 5,
              "operator": {
                "type": "number",
                "operation": "gte"
              }
            }
          ],
          "combinator": "and"
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "3f8c9af2-57ef-4a93-8427-1e8d6c745471",
      "name": "Check if 5+ Fulfillment Reviews",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2.3,
      "position": [
        2704,
        400
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const reviews = $input.first().json.fulfilment_items;\nconst MAX_CHARS = 20000; // ~5,000 tokens per chunk, safe limit\n\nconst chunks = [];\nlet currentChunk = [];\nlet currentLength = 0;\nlet chunkIndex = 1;\n\nfor (const review of reviews) {\n  const formatted = `Title: ${review.title}\nText: ${review.text}\nRating: ${review.rating}/5\nDate: ${review.publishedDate}\nbusinessUrl: ${review.businessUrl}`;\n\n  const reviewLength = formatted.length;\n\n  // If adding this review exceeds limit, save current chunk and start new one\n  if (currentLength + reviewLength > MAX_CHARS && currentChunk.length > 0) {\n    chunks.push({\n      json: {\n        chunk_index: chunkIndex++,\n        review_count: currentChunk.length,\n        char_count: currentLength,\n        formatted_text: currentChunk.join('\\n\\n---\\n\\n')\n      }\n    });\n    currentChunk = [];\n    currentLength = 0;\n  }\n\n  currentChunk.push(formatted);\n  currentLength += reviewLength;\n}\n\n// Push the last remaining chunk\nif (currentChunk.length > 0) {\n  chunks.push({\n    json: {\n      chunk_index: chunkIndex,\n      review_count: currentChunk.length,\n      char_count: currentLength,\n      formatted_text: currentChunk.join('\\n\\n---\\n\\n')\n    }\n  });\n}\n\nreturn chunks;"
      },
      "id": "a58a266c-27f5-43fa-a00c-ef7c0c237530",
      "name": "Chunk Reviews for AI",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        2928,
        304
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=\nnumber of fulfillment relevant reviews: {{ $json.review_count }}\n\nFulfilment related Reviews Data:{{ $json.formatted_text }}\n\nAssume the role of a perishable product direct-to-consumer fulfillment company leveraging TrustPilot reviews to identify an approach strategy. Prospect companies will either be fulfilling and shipping their products directly to consumers themselves or outsourcing the fulfillment and shipping to a perishable product fulfillment company. Poor reviews mentioning issues with packaging, product thawing or wet, damage, or missing items will indicate a company with an inclination to consider a new perishable fulfillment solution provider.\nConsider the date ranges of the reviews to see if the packages received are improving or declining. Declining sentiment indicates a company with an inclination to consider a new perishable fulfillment solution provider.\n\n\nFor each theme, capture:\n\n\n\nPattern — the operational issue or strength in 5–8 words (e.g. \"Coolant depleted on 2-day ground deliveries to West Coast\")\nFrequency — how many reviews mention it\nSeverity signal — verbatim language strength (\"disgusting,\" \"ruined,\" \"perfect every time\") and star ratings of contributing reviews\nRecency — concentrated in last 30/60/90 days, or spread across longer period\nOne representative pull quote — short, verbatim, no editing\n\n\n\nRanking the top 3\nRank concerns and strengths independently. Use this hierarchy:\n-Frequency — patterns mentioned by the most reviewers rank higher\n-Severity — patterns with stronger language or lower star ratings break frequency ties\n-Recency — recent patterns rank higher than old ones at equal weight (current operational reality matters more than historical)\n-Operational specificity — \"boxes arrived warm\" beats \"shipping issues\"; specific patterns are more actionable for sales than generic ones\n\nWhat to do when data is thin\n\n\n\nFewer than 5 fulfillment-relevant reviews: report insufficient_data for that side (concerns or strengths). Do not invent patterns to fill three slots.\nReviews exist but heavily one-sided (e.g. all positive, no concerns): return what's actually there. Empty arrays are valid and useful.\nAmbiguous fragments: when a review says \"delivery was bad\" with no detail, count it toward a generic logistics concern but don't fabricate the specific failure mode.\n\nTrend can only be any of these options Improving/Stable/Declining/New Baseline\nOnly include logistics or packaging themes if explicitly mentioned in reviews. Do not infer delivery, shipping, packaging, or freshness unless directly referenced.\nKeep each theme field to a maximum of 10 words per theme, semicolon-separated, no numbering.\nReturn ONLY valid enum values for these fields.\n\noverall_sentiment:\n- Positive\n- Neutral\n- Mixed\n- Negative\n- Insufficient Data\n\nmatched_status:\n- Auto-matched\n- Matched-no reviews\n- Needs review\n\ntrend:\n- Improving\n- Stable\n- Declining\n- New Baseline\n\nDo not add explanations, punctuation, or extra text to enum fields.\nPut all explanations in sentiment_summary or recommendation_approach.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "batching": {
            "batchSize": 1,
            "delayBetweenBatches": 5000
          }
        }
      },
      "id": "a0cc4aeb-7896-479b-bc8d-5cd5559375f5",
      "name": "Analyze Review Chunks",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        3152,
